.SH NAME
drm_helper_connector_dpms \- connector dpms helper implementation
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" drm_helper_connector_dpms
.BI "(struct drm_connector *connector "  ","
.BI "int mode "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "connector" 12
affected connector
.IP "mode" 12
DPMS mode
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
The \fBdrm_helper_connector_dpms\fP helper function implements the
\fIdrm_connector_funcs.dpms\fP callback for drivers using the legacy CRTC
helpers.

This is the main helper function provided by the CRTC helper framework for
implementing the DPMS connector attribute. It computes the new desired DPMS
state for all encoders and CRTCs in the output mesh and calls the
\fIdrm_crtc_helper_funcs.dpms\fP and \fIdrm_encoder_helper_funcs.dpms\fP callbacks
provided by the driver.

This function is deprecated.  New drivers must implement atomic modeset
support, where DPMS is handled in the DRM core.
.SH "RETURN"
Always returns 0.
